<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881115-0011 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief -- Allegheny International Inc.: Firm Agrees to Sell Unit Under Restructuring Moves </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AG SVGI </CO><IN> TNM BCY </IN><TEXT>   Allegheny International Inc., Pittsburgh, said it has reached a definitive purchase agreement to sell its Thermco Systems Inc. subsidiary to Silicon Valley Group Inc. Terms weren't disclosed.    Allegheny, which has filed for protection under Chapter 11 of the federal Bankruptcy Code, has been selling off businesses unrelated to its core consumer products operations as part of a restructuring and to raise cash.    Thermco, Orange, Calif., makes production systems for the semiconductor industry. Silicon Valley Group is a San Jose, Calif., supplier of production processing equipment for that industry. </TEXT></DOC>